column5: C'mon show a little class boys, we're better than that.  What a beauty though! Glad to see Reimer playing well,and I'm just loving Jake Gardiner, what a great young player.
Gardiner has a solid future ahead of him.  6 losses in a row, hahahaha
It's fun to poke fun at the Ottawa fans once in a while Mike!  lol
Sens suck!!!   Go Leafs!  Where's that Matt guy???

Well, as much as I would have preferred a different outcome, I can say my Sens were outperformed by the Leafs tonight. I'm humbled, but not too disappointed seeing as this is a rebuilding year and the season series is now tied at 2-2.  My sens did suck tonight, badly, and deserved to lose. There...I admitted it  All that said, the sens still have a long way to go to suck as bad as the leafs...what is it anyways??? Like 46years....  Enjoy it while it's there boys...your leafs did good tonight!(but still suck)
1926-27 was the senators last cup, so I would say it's the other way around, good luck in the next 15 years, centuries go by quick.....
On a side note...take a look at where Montreal is in the standings.  Yikes, Habs fans will be jumping off roofs soon!
A Tom Petty song comes to mind.
Well when they hit the ground they'll be landing on the Coach and the GM.   Not too much "Nah Nah Hey Hey" in habs land these days! Dan O.
